---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout
  title="MCP Server Card Guide | Is It Agent Ready?"
  description="Publish an MCP server card so agents can discover your MCP tools, transport endpoint, authentication model, and capabilities."
  canonical="https://isitagentready.com/checks/mcp-server-card"
>
  <section class="card" style="padding: 28px;">
    <h1 class="section-title">MCP server card</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      An MCP server card gives agents a structured way to understand your MCP endpoint before connecting. It should describe your server metadata, transport, authentication, and available tools.
    </p>
    <pre>{`{
  "serverInfo": {
    "name": "example-mcp",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
  "transport": {
    "type": "streamable-http",
    "endpoint": "/mcp"
  },
  "authentication": {
    "required": false
  }
}`}</pre>
    <p class="muted">
      Draft reference:
      <a class="link" href="https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol/pull/2127" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> MCP Server Card</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
